Package genSynthFlow

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AreaWorkingCounts
    Working counts of flows from each area (OA).
    CandOAsPerWZ
    Candidate OAs that are within specified distance interval of a single specified WZ.
    GenSynthFlow
    GenSynthFlow is the top level class for a small application to generate synthetic origin-destination commuter flow data based on constraints derived from 2011 Census of England and Wales data.
    SynthPop
    Creates a synthetic population of workers travelling from OAs to WZs.
    Worker
    Single "synthetic" commuter characteristics
    ZoneFlow
    OA or WZ flow as extracted from 2011 Census-derived CSV Files For each WZ or OA read in from CSV: zoneCode eastingPWC northingPWC distCounts[DIST_INTERVALS]
    ZoneFlowList
    Array of ZoneFlow (2 instances: OAs, WZs)
